==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-yarmulke.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
From the [[w:Yiddish language|Yiddish]] (''yarmlke''), from the [[w:Polish language|Polish]] ''[[jarmułka]]'' and the [[w:Ukrainean language|Ukrainean]] (''yarmulka''), ''[[skullcap]].'' This may derive from the [[w:Turkish language|Turkish]] (''yağmurluk''), that is ''[[rainwear]].'' A more likely possibility (given the East European origin of the word, and the lack of waterproofness of the skullcaps in question) is that it derives from the [[w:Hebrew language|Hebrew]] phrase ('yarei me'eloko'), ''fearer of God'', a reference to the religious reason for wearing such a headcovering. This [[term]] entered English in 1903.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A skullcap worn by [[religious]] [[Jewish]] males (especially during [[prayer]]), also known as a [[kippah]].

